<topic id="webhelp-customization-add-image-to-title">
  <title>Adding a Logo Image in the Title Area</title>
  <prolog>
    <metadata>
      <keywords>
        <indexterm>Customizing WebHelp Systems <indexterm>add logo image in title
          area</indexterm></indexterm>
      </keywords>
    </metadata>
  </prolog>
  <body>
      <p>You can customize the title area of your WebHelp output by using a custom CSS.</p>
    <p>For example, to add a logo image before the title, you could use the following code:</p>
      <codeblock outputclass="language-css">#header  h1:before {
    display:inline;
    content:url('oxygen-webhelp/resources/img/myLogoImage.gif');
}</codeblock>
    <p>In the example above, <b>myLogoImage.gif</b> is an image file that needs to be stored in an
      images directory, where it will be automatically copied to the output directory by the WebHelp
      transformation.</p>
    <p><ph
        conref="../reusables/topics/reusable-webhelp-customizing.dita#reusable-webhelp-customizing/image-files-folder-ph"
        /><ul id="ul_efm_f12_vs">
        <li><ph
            conref="../reusables/topics/reusable-webhelp-customizing.dita#reusable-webhelp-customizing/DITA-image-path-ph"
          /></li>
        <li><ph
            conref="../reusables/topics/reusable-webhelp-customizing.dita#reusable-webhelp-customizing/DocBook-image-path-ph"
          /></li>
      </ul></p>
    <p>Then you need to specify the path of your custom CSS in the transformation scenario.</p>
    <p><ph
        conref="../reusables/topics/reusable-webhelp-customizing.dita#reusable-webhelp-customizing/transform-parameters-tab-ph"
        /><ul id="ul_wnh_m12_vs">
        <li><ph
            conref="../reusables/topics/reusable-webhelp-customizing.dita#reusable-webhelp-customizing/DITA-parameters-ph"
          /></li>
        <li><ph
            conref="../reusables/topics/reusable-webhelp-customizing.dita#reusable-webhelp-customizing/DocBook-parameters-ph"
          /></li>
      </ul></p>
  </body>
